In July of 2020 we sat under this banyan tree 

We asked for magic 

We were oblivious to the pain we would face together in such a short, frenetic period of time. 
Unaware of the work and sacrifices the relationship would require from us but intoxicated off of the love. And the karma. 

Somehow a year and a half later, having walked through hell together, and having laughed more than I ever imagined possible, he asked me to marry him.

So I‚Äôve never done a sponsored post before but I‚Äôve researched and tested these @truwomen bars and feel like I can give you an honest review.
.
.
.
First- planning what I‚Äôm going to eat consumes a ridiculous amount of my time because of all the foods that I avoid (No gluten! No gmo! No canola oil! No xylitol or erythritol! And many many more). I oscillate between eating keto and paleo. When I‚Äôm eating paleo I need snacks that I can bring with me to work or while traveling. Most protein bars contain inflammatory ingredients and so I usually avoid them. But I can sign off on the ingredients in these, and the carbohydrate profile is low enough that I could make these work even in ketosis.
.
.
.
Second- they taste great. Obviously an important factor. They‚Äôre not chalky or too crumbly, the consistency is appealing, and they‚Äôre not too sweet. I Scream For Orange Cream is our favorite which brings me to...
.
.
.
Third- I keep my kids on a low sugar diet and they are obsessed with these because they think they‚Äôre candy bars. I keep them in my backpack and when my kids start fighting in the car (instantly upon entering said car) I give them these and they‚Äôre quiet for like three entire minutes! An eternity for parents with multiple kids.
.
.
.
So all in all I‚Äôm comfortable recommending these to you guys. Great taste, clean ingredients, guilt free and convenient for stressed out moms with human hurricanes for children. #truwomen
